            <p>Urinary Catheters are flexible tubes designed to empty the bladder during urinary incontinence or urinary retention by collecting the urine in a drainage bag (NHS)</p>
            <p><b>Allow urine drainage during:</b></p>
            <div class="catheterbox">Prostate enlargement or scarring</div>
            <div class="catheterbox">Weakness or nerve damage</div>
            <div class="catheterbox">Post-childbirth incontinence</div>
            <div class="catheterbox">Bladder cancer or chemotherapy</div>
        </div>
